WARNING: Do not edit this file! It is used by 1st Word Plus "Extra Help"
[OK|CANCEL]
Use OPEN FILE to create or|edit a file in a window - up|to four can be open at once.
Use PRINT FILE to select a|file for printing - remember|to use SAVE FILE first.
Use SAVE FILE to save the file|in the current window to disk|and to close the window.
Use SAVE AS to save the file|in the current window to disk|with a new name.
Use SAVE & RESUME to save|the file in the current window|without finishing the edit.
Use READ FILE to insert a|complete file from disk at the|current window cursor position.
Use WRITE BLOCK to save the|contents of the marked block|in the window to a disk file.
Use DELETE FILE to erase a|file from disk permanently,|for example to make room to|SAVE a file.
Use QUIT to close the|window without saving the text|or to exit to the GEM Desktop.
Use QUIT ALL to close all|windows without saving the|text and then exit to the|GEM Desktop.
Use FIND to search for a text|string within the window and|to move the cursor there.
Use REPLACE to search for a|text string and replace it|with a second text string.
Use REPEAT FIND to repeat the|previous FIND or REPLACE|from the cursor position.
Use STATISTICS to find out|the size of a document|or the remaining space|in RAM and on disk.
Use WP MODE for document text|only - turn it off for editing|program sources or data files.
Switch on HYPHENATION to make|REFORMAT pause when you should|hyphenate a word.
Use INSERT MODE to show if the|text you type must be inserted|or must overwrite the old text.
Use WORD WRAP to show if you|want 1st Word Plus to wrap|words at the right margin onto|the next line.
Use SET MARK to remember a|position in the current window|so you can GOTO MARK later.
Use GOTO MARK to return to a|position in the text that you|have remembered with SET MARK.
Use GOTO PAGE or GOTO LINE|to move to the start of|the specified page or line.
Use START BLOCK to define or|modify the start position of a|block - then use END BLOCK.
Use END BLOCK to define or|modify the end position of a|block - use after START BLOCK.
Use CUT BLOCK to copy the text|in the block to the clipboard|so that you can PASTE BLOCK|later.
Use PASTE BLOCK to copy the|text on the clipboard to the|window at the cursor position.
Use COPY BLOCK to copy the|text in the block to the|window at the cursor position.
Use MOVE BLOCK to move the|text in the block to the|window at the cursor position.
Use DELETE BLOCK to delete the|text in the current marked|block - permanently.
Use FIND START to move the|cursor in the window to the|start of the marked block.
Use FIND END to move the|cursor in the window to the|end of the marked block.
Use HIDE BLOCK to unmark|the current marked block.
Switch on SHOW RULER to|display the current margins|and tab points.
Switch on SHOW POSITION to|display the current page,|line and column numbers.
Use PAGE LAYOUT to define the|page layout and the head and|foot lines for your document.
Use ADD RULER to specify text|pitch, ruler length, line|spacing, tab spacing, and|justify mode for the following|text.
Use DELETE RULER to delete|the current text ruler.
Use READ RULER to add the|first ruler found in the|file specified.
Use FOOTNOTE FORMAT to define|the arrangement of the rule|which separates the footnotes|from the text.
Use ADD FOOTNOTE to add a|footnote number at the cursor|position and to enter the|footnote text.
Use BOLD before typing text|that you want to see in bold|and before a RESTYLE command.
Use UNDERLINE before typing|text that you want to see|underlined and before RESTYLE.
Use ITALIC before typing text|that you want to see in italic|and before a RESTYLE command.
Use LIGHT before typing text|that you want to see in light|and before a RESTYLE command.
Use SUPERSCRIPT before typing|text that you want to see in|superscript and before RESTYLE.
Use SUBSCRIPT before typing|text that you want to see in|subscript and before RESTYLE.
Use RESTYLE to changed the|text style of a marked block|to the style options selected.
Use CENTRE to position an|existing line halfway between|the left and right margins.
Use RIGHT to position an|existing line flush with the|right margin.
Use INDENT to define your|paragraph indent size before|typing or a REFORMAT command.
Use REFORMAT to rejustify part|or all of your document after|you have altered text or|modified a ruler.
Use LOAD DICTIONARY to read|in the spelling dictionary.
Use CHECK SPELLING to search|for typing or spelling|mistakes in your document.
Switch on CONTINUOUS CHECK|to check each word as it|is typed in.
Use BROWSE to look at the|words held in the spelling|dictionary.
Use ADD WORD to add a new|word to the supplementary|dictionary.
Use END SPELL CHECK when the|dictionary is no longer|required, and to save updates.
Use GRAPHICS MODE to allow|pictures to be merged|with the text.
Use READ PICTURE to read a|picture into the text at the|cursor position.
Use DELETE PICTURE to delete|the picture at the cursor|position.

